{
  "texts": [
    "The answers to each question were on a 5-point Likert scale, and for each participant, the scores of the questions related to that domain were averaged.",
    "A final score was calculated as the mean score of all fields.Shapiro-Wilk Normality Test was used to confirm the normality of data distribution for statistical tests.",
    "The Scores were compared between groups with a t-test and Mann-Whitney U test.",
    "The correlation analyses were carried out with Spearman's Rank Correlation method.",
    "Results DemographicsFour hundred seventy-six (476) university students studying in 7 academic disciplines of health-related sciences at the same university participated in the study."
  ]
}